Part 3 - Flavour Bases - Chinese Kung Pao Chicken. This is such an addictive dish!!! Chinese flavour bases will routinely include garlic, fresh ginger, spring onions, chillies and shallots (not white or brown onions). Chinese five-spice and star anise are also among the â€˜basicsâ€™.
ï»¿-
ï»¿Kung Pao is in the range of â€˜stickyâ€™ Chinese dishes. If youâ€™ve had Chinese Lemon Chicken, then youâ€™ll know how that tastes.
ï»¿-
ï»¿There are hundreds if not thousands of Kung Pao recipes. I like Diane Kuanâ€™s flavour base (from Epicurious), which tracks with the flavour bases pictured on the Fine Dining Lovers website.
ï»¿-
Iâ€™ve listed the ingredients of the base here, but not the full recipe, as you might want to try this with a different food.

CHEESE RAVA CUTLET ğŸ¤¤ğŸ¤¤ğŸ¤¤
. 
. 
. 
. 
Ingredients

â–¢1 1/2Â CupÂ Milk

â–¢1/2Â CupÂ chopped onion

â–¢1/2Â CupÂ grated cheese

â–¢1Â tablespoonÂ chopped coriander

â–¢1Â CupÂ rava/soojiÂ (Semolina)

â–¢1Â teaspoonÂ Italian Herbs (organo and chilli flakes)

â–¢1Â teaspoonÂ black pepper or to taste

â–¢Salt to taste

â–¢2 â€“ 3Â tablespoonÂ cooking oil

Instructions

Boil milk in a pan. Add cheese cubes, chopped onion, Italian seasoning and stir to combine.

Once the cheese is melted, slowly add the semolina. Continuously stir the mixture. Turn off the heat.

Now add the salt, pepper, and coriander. Continuously stir the mixture until it reaches a thick spreading consistency. Set aside.

Grease a square tray with butter.

Spread the semolina mixture on the tray. Keep the thickness of half inch. Gently press it with the spatula.

Set it aside for one hour or till it is set. You can also keep it in the fridge for 30 minutes.

Cut the cutlets into the desired shapes using a knife or a cookie cutter.

You can serve them as it is or pan fry for a crispy texture. You can store these cutlets in the fridge for a week. Reheat or pan fry whenever required.

To pan fry the rava cutlets, heat 2 tablespoon of oil in a pan.

Fry the cutlets till they turn crisp from both the sides.

Serve Cheese Rava Cutlets warm with your favoriteÂ chutneyÂ or ketchup.

Raspberry & Avocado Salad With Sweet Dressing ğŸ˜‹ 

My fave salad is definitely an avo one. This dressing is the best as its nice and sweet but balanced with the pomegranate juice. 
You can add anything additional to the salad such as cucumbers, peppers, croutons etc. But this is a simple version.

Ingredients:

â€¢	2 Avocados (skin removed and chopped into small chunks 
â€¢	Around 100g raspberry's (or as many as you like)
â€¢	6 Baby gem lettuce leaves (washed and dried)
â€¢	5 cherry tomatoes (Washed and cut in half)

Dressing:

â€¢	Â½ cup olive oil
â€¢	1 Â½ tbs agave
â€¢	2 tbs Pomegranate 
â€¢	1 tbs fresh lemon juice
â€¢	1 tsp wholegrain mustard
â€¢	Sesame seeds
â€¢	Dash of salt and Pepper

Method

1.	Lay down your baby gems and pop over the rest of the ingredients 
2.	Drizzle with dressing & serve immediately
